if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/The_Protagonist_and_Mark_walk_together_their_conversation_easy_and_comfortable.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Celestine and Mark walk together, their conversation easy and comfortable.
	Mark: So B.C. is the Principal. The mysterious guide was literally running the school.
	Mark: Hidden in plain sight the whole time.
	Celestine: The best hiding place often is. No one suspects the obvious.
	Mark: Do you think anyone else knows? About B.C.?
	Celestine: Probably not. The Principal keeps their dual role separate for good reason.
	Celestine: As Principal, they handle immediate problems. As B.C., they plant seeds for long-term growth.
	Celestine: Both roles are necessary. Both serve students.
	Mark: And now you're part of that. Helping students learn and grow.
	Celestine: In my own way, yes.
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/The_Protagonist_and_Mark_walk_together_their_conversation_easy_and_comfortable.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
