[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/They_stop_near_a_bench_where_a_student_sits_alone_looking_troubled.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
They stop near a bench where a student sits alone, looking troubled.
Mark: That's Ben. From the exam case. He looks stressed.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: He does. Should I talk to him?
	Mark: That's your call. You're the guide now, remember?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/The_Protagonist_considers_then_approaches_gently.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Celestine considers, then approaches gently.
	join characters/Ben center
	Celestine: Hey, Ben. You okay?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/Ben_looks_up_surprised_but_relieved.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Ben looks up, surprised but relieved.
	Ben: Celestine. Actually... I've been struggling with something.
	Ben: My friend asked me to cover for him during practice. Said he needs to skip for something important.
	Ben: But I know the coach will ask me directly if he was there. And I don't want to lie.
	Celestine: So you're torn between helping your friend and being honest.
	Ben: Exactly. What would you do?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/The_Protagonist_pauses_Old_The_Protagonist_might_have_told_you_the_answer.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Celestine pauses. Old Celestine might have told him the answer.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/New_The_Protagonist_understands_better.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	New Celestine understands better.
	Celestine: I can't make that choice for you, Ben. It's yours to make.
	Celestine: But I can help you think through it.
	Celestine: What happens if you lie for him? What happens if you refuse?
	Celestine: What values matter most to you? Loyalty? Honesty?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/Ben_thinks_carefully.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Ben thinks carefully.
	Ben: I... I think I need to tell him I can't lie for him. But I can help him figure out another way.
	Ben: Maybe we can talk to the coach together, explain why he needs to miss practice.
	Celestine: That sounds like a solution that respects both honesty and friendship.
	Ben: Thanks, Celestine. I just needed to talk it through.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s5/Ben_walks_away_looking_more_confident.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Ben walks away, looking more confident.
	leave characters/Ben
	Mark: You did it. You didn't solve his problem for him.
	Mark: You helped him solve it himself.
	Celestine: That's the lesson B.C. taught me. People grow when they make their own choices.
	Celestine: I can guide. I can ask questions. But the choice is theirs.
else:
